{title: Down At The End Of Memory Lane}
{artist: Jimmie Davis}
{composer: Written by Jimmie Davis and Robert Anthony Jones}

[C]Down at the end of [F]Memory lane
[C]Where many have walked it in [G7]gladness
[C]But I am the one to [F]walk it last
I [C]walked it [G7]alone in sad[C]ness
[F]I received a letter from my [C]darling
I opened it and this is what she [G7]said
[C]I’m sorry if I hurt you but [F]now it is too late
[C]For another man my [G7]darling I have [C]wed
I remember her [F]sweet little face
[C]And her pretty eyes of [G7]blue
[C]Golden hair [F]hanging down her back
[C]Tied with a [G7]big blue ribbon [C]bow
[F]We were childhood chums together [C]there
I loved her with all my heart and [G7]soul
But [C]she left me for another [F]without a thought or care
And [C]she left me in this [G7]world alone and [C]cold